author: @markd5928
text: If anyone else is attempting this in Jupyter and encountering a "this event loop is already running" error, it's a nested loop problem. The fix is installing the nest_asyncio package... conda install -c conda-forge nest-asyncio ...and then running the following lines before¬†launching the tutorial¬†code: import nest_asyncio nest_asyncio.apply()This link was helpful in diagnosing the problem:https://markhneedham.com/blog/2019/05/10/jupyter-runtimeerror-this-event-loop-is-already-running/

author: @vichnaiev
text: Your explanation of the distribute_workers function is 100% wrong. What it actually does is make sure that you don't have too many workers on the same base and also on the same gas geyser. So, if you have more than 16 on a base it should send workers to another expansion. If you have more than 3 workers on a single geyser it will find a different one for you. It has absolutely no relation to the "mineral patch".
